messages.title: Believing in our NHS
messages.content: The NHS is the Labour Party's greatest achievement. We created it, saved it, value it and will always support it. The NHS still needs to improve, but you can be sure I'll be campaigning for these.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: Labour aims to support the NHS which includes improving local health services and resisting privatisation and charges.

issues.health: The NHS still needs to improve, but you can be sure I'll be campaigning for these.

quotes.text: Sadly, the Conservative candidate says the NHS belongs 'in Stalin's Russia' and wants it replaced by private insurance and charges.

For Mr Bone got his way, an average family in Wellingborough on £30,000 a year would have to fork out more than £1,500 in health charges and insurance. So much for David Cameron's 'we're all in this together'.

images.caption: Jayne with local residents supporting the NHS
